Steps:
1) Read idea.md.
2) Inspect the LaTeX template (find the main entry .tex).
3) Explore project_dir to locate the results directory (bash find). IMPORTANT: when using bash, set working_dir=project_dir.
4) If an experiment workspace is provided, also read its specs/report/feedback files (absolute paths listed in system prompt).
5) Produce an academic paper structure + section design (intent/key points/evidence/artifacts/failure paths).
6) Encode subagent orchestration rules (analysis/viz/literature/review triggers).
7) Write outputs using write_file() to the ABSOLUTE paths below.
8) Verify both outputs using file_viewer().

